<i>all alone again ♪</i>

02:01.125 --> 02:02.751
Alan, Alan.

02:02.834 --> 02:04.542
Hey, what's up, Dad?
Uh, you're boarding
in a few minutes.

02:04.626 --> 02:06.250
I'm gonna go
find your mother.
Dad, relax.

02:06.334 --> 02:07.959
She just doesn't want us
to see her crying.

02:08.042 --> 02:09.834
So she went to the bathroom
to cry in front of strangers.

02:10.500 --> 02:12.125
How about you, Dad?

02:12.209 --> 02:13.792
You sad to see me
finally leave home?

02:13.876 --> 02:15.709
Look, Alan,
you're going aboard
for the first time.

02:15.792 --> 02:17.000
You're gonna be
in a foreign country.

02:17.083 --> 02:20.042
You might even, you know,
go to Amsterdam.

02:20.125 --> 02:21.459
And, you know,
just... Just...

02:21.542 --> 02:22.792
European women
are different.

02:22.876 --> 02:24.334
How do you know?

02:24.417 --> 02:26.417
James Bond films, mostly,
but, that doesn't...

02:26.500 --> 02:27.918
Guys, look at mommy!

02:28.000 --> 02:30.334
Oh, that was so cute.

02:30.417 --> 02:31.751
Hi, honey.
Hi.

02:31.834 --> 02:33.626
Dad here was starting to
get worried about you.

02:33.709 --> 02:35.542
Oh, daddy should
worry about himself.

02:35.626 --> 02:37.709
He can't admit how much
he's gonna miss you.

02:37.792 --> 02:39.334
See, that's the difference
between us.

02:39.417 --> 02:41.209
I get it out
and I let it go,

02:41.292 --> 02:42.500
and he gets a headache.

02:42.584 --> 02:43.792
Well, maybe I wouldn't
get a headache

02:43.876 --> 02:45.834
if you didn't get it out
and let it go.

02:45.918 --> 02:47.792
You get a headache
because you don't
express your feelings,

02:47.876 --> 02:49.167
and that's why you
grind your teeth.

02:49.250 --> 02:50.500
Guys...
Well, maybe I...

02:50.584 --> 02:51.542
Can we not have
this moment?

02:51.626 --> 02:53.167
Oh, okay, sorry.

02:53.250 --> 02:54.667
Could you take
that, sweetie?

02:54.751 --> 02:56.417
Look, I've got
something for you.

02:56.500 --> 02:58.751
It is an international
beeper.

02:58.834 --> 03:00.209
And all you have to do
is press that little button,

03:00.292 --> 03:01.667
and anywhere you
are on the planet,

03:01.751 --> 03:03.792
it will ring on
my corresponding unit.

03:03.876 --> 03:05.959
And then what?
And then I'll call you.

03:06.042 --> 03:07.918
And if you don't answer,
she'll fly over.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.209
MAN ON PA: <i>Charter flight 178</i>
<i>to London</i>

03:10.292 --> 03:12.250
<i>is now boarding
at Gate 50-b.</i>

03:12.334 --> 03:13.876
<i>All Ohio State students</i>

03:13.959 --> 03:15.250
<i>should have their
boarding cards ready.</i>

03:15.334 --> 03:16.876
So, I guess
this is it.

03:19.459 --> 03:21.876
Give your mother a big hug.
She's very fragile today.

03:24.459 --> 03:25.667
I think daddy's
a wreck, okay,

03:25.751 --> 03:28.542
so make sure
you call him, okay?

03:30.459 --> 03:32.083
Okay...

03:32.167 --> 03:34.000
You guys take care
of each other.

04:06.000 --> 04:07.500
I was really proud
of you back there.

04:07.584 --> 04:09.000
I thought you
were gonna lose it.

04:09.083 --> 04:11.542
Yeah, so was I.
I guess I'm stronger
than I think.

04:11.626 --> 04:13.167
And, look
at it this way,

04:13.250 --> 04:14.459
we have more time
to ourselves now.

04:14.542 --> 04:17.000
Just us.
Just you and me,

04:17.083 --> 04:19.709
alone in the house.

04:24.125 --> 04:25.167
It's okay, it's okay.

04:25.834 --> 04:26.918
I'm sorry.

04:28.083 --> 04:30.000
You know,
you should be excited
about this interview.

04:30.083 --> 04:32.000
If it goes well,
we're moving to New York.

04:32.083 --> 04:34.167
We'll have more money,
and we'll have
that "New York" money.

04:34.250 --> 04:36.500
I don't want any more
money, Henry.

04:36.584 --> 04:38.918
You've been at Sellinski
for 23 years.

04:39.000 --> 04:40.542
You have a good job,

04:40.626 --> 04:43.584
and we've lived in Ohio
all our lives.

04:43.667 --> 04:45.751
Besides, I thought
you hated New York.

04:45.834 --> 04:47.584
I only hated New York
when it was hip
to hate New York.

04:47.667 --> 04:49.209
Now it's not hip
to hate it anymore,

04:49.292 --> 04:51.042
so I don't hate it.
I'm in advertising.

04:51.125 --> 04:52.959
I'm weak, and
I follow the crowd.

04:53.042 --> 04:56.542
Well, I guess we
could see Susan more.

04:56.626 --> 04:58.500
Maybe you can.
She won't speak to me.

04:58.584 --> 04:59.918
Well, yeah, I mean,
you know,

05:00.000 --> 05:02.417
when she calls up and says
she's having second thoughts
about med school

05:02.500 --> 05:04.000
and you blow up at her,
I mean, it's like...

05:04.083 --> 05:06.250
I didn't blow up at her.
Yes, you did, Henry.

05:06.334 --> 05:07.709
I did not.
I merely told her

05:07.792 --> 05:09.542
that I was
going to sue her.

05:09.626 --> 05:12.209
Oh, you can't sue your own
daughter for lost tuition.

05:12.292 --> 05:13.417
You can now.
You can.

05:13.500 --> 05:15.042
No, there's
that precedent.

05:15.125 --> 05:16.792
It's <i>Mr. Brown vs.</i>
<i>Muffy the daughter.</i>
Oh, my God!

05:55.709 --> 05:57.751
Yeah, hang on.
Hang on one second.

06:02.167 --> 06:04.375
Yeah, Tony,
yeah, thanks.

06:04.459 --> 06:05.500
Thanks for setting up
that meeting.

06:05.584 --> 06:07.751
I'm going, 10:00.

06:09.000 --> 06:11.209
Tony, I can't tell Nancy
I was fired.

06:12.417 --> 06:13.792
I know.

06:13.876 --> 06:15.542
I know, it's
very caveman of me,

06:15.626 --> 06:17.876
but that's what
I've decided...

06:17.959 --> 06:19.375
Yeah, well,
you're not Nancy.

06:20.417 --> 06:22.918
Okay, but listen,
I appreciate it.

06:23.000 --> 06:24.375
Okay, thanks, bye.

06:40.083 --> 06:41.959
There's too much food.

06:44.167 --> 06:45.167
No, there's not.

06:45.250 --> 06:47.000
I could never get enough
to eat when Alan was here.

06:47.083 --> 06:49.834
Now, pass me those
potatoes, baby.

06:49.918 --> 06:52.667
This is fantastic.
We never get
a chance to talk.

06:52.751 --> 06:54.709
When the kids were here,
we only talked about them.

06:54.792 --> 06:56.500
Now we get
to talk about us.

06:56.584 --> 06:58.834
I mean,
this is a gab-fest.

06:58.918 --> 07:00.751
Yak-yak-yak-yak-yak.

07:01.334 --> 07:02.751
So...

07:04.667 --> 07:05.876
Uh...

07:09.000 --> 07:10.375
What's going on with you?

07:12.500 --> 07:16.292
I have absolutely no idea
what I'm going to do
with the rest of my life.

07:18.000 --> 07:20.042
I can't even decide
whether I should go
to New York with you

07:20.125 --> 07:22.918
for that interview.
I'd just be tagging along

07:23.000 --> 07:26.542
out of pure panic
and insecurity.

07:26.626 --> 07:29.334
You know, but it's ironic
that the minute we have

07:29.417 --> 07:32.334
time together that we, like,
immediately separate.

07:33.709 --> 07:35.918
Although, if we force
ourselves to be together

07:36.000 --> 07:38.209
instead of letting it
happen naturally,

07:38.292 --> 07:40.918
what are we proving?

07:41.584 --> 07:43.083
Well,

07:44.834 --> 07:46.417
I don't know what
to tell you, baby.

07:54.375 --> 07:55.792
I gotta pack.

08:00.667 --> 08:01.918
Good morning, sir.

08:02.000 --> 08:03.918
How are you?
I'm fine, thank you.

08:06.626 --> 08:07.751
(CAR DOORS SHUTTING)

08:07.834 --> 08:09.834
(ENGINE STARTING)

08:25.083 --> 08:27.083
FLIGHT ATTENDANT:
<i>Welcome aboard</i>
<i>Tri-State Air Flight 42</i>

08:27.167 --> 08:28.375
<i>to New York.</i>

08:28.459 --> 08:31.000
<i>If you'd make sure
your seat belts are
securely fastened,</i>

08:31.083 --> 08:32.709
<i>we'll be able
to pull away...</i>

08:32.792 --> 08:34.083
Uhh!
Ohh!

08:34.167 --> 08:35.292
(CRASH)

08:37.083 --> 08:38.167
Ohh!

08:42.542 --> 08:43.792
Surprise!

08:55.709 --> 08:56.834
Henry?

08:58.626 --> 08:59.792
Henry?

09:02.417 --> 09:04.042
Henry!

09:04.125 --> 09:06.834
What?
Are you excited I came?

09:07.792 --> 09:09.667
What?
Are you excited I came?

09:11.834 --> 09:13.375
I'm very excited.

09:15.792 --> 09:18.083
'Cause you don't
sound excited, Henry.

09:19.751 --> 09:21.209
I'm holding it in.

09:21.292 --> 09:23.876
He's excited.
We're all excited, okay?

09:23.959 --> 09:26.500
Oh, Henry, you forgot
your foot chums.

09:27.876 --> 09:29.500
What?
Your foot chums.

09:29.584 --> 09:31.125
Aah!

09:31.209 --> 09:32.876
Here, could you pass
these down, please,

09:32.959 --> 09:34.417
over there to that man?

09:35.209 --> 09:36.918
No, that's...

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
Oh, and he
always forgets this.

09:39.083 --> 09:41.042
For the whole trip,
he'll be complaining
about his rash.

09:41.125 --> 09:42.834
Could you pass that down?
For the next two days,

09:42.918 --> 09:45.292
it's gonna be scratch,
scratch, scratch,

09:45.375 --> 09:46.584
flake, flake, flake.

09:47.500 --> 09:48.751
(GASPS)

09:48.834 --> 09:50.292
MAN: Let them
sit together.

09:50.375 --> 09:51.918
Thanks.

09:52.834 --> 09:54.250
Here we go.

09:54.334 --> 09:56.584
Oh, uh, sorry.
We're not gonna be eating.
Okay.

09:56.667 --> 09:58.500
Don't you think
we should have a little
something, Henry?

09:58.584 --> 10:00.834
Baby, we're gonna be eating
in one of the great hotels
in the world.

10:00.918 --> 10:02.167
You don't
want to ruin that

10:02.250 --> 10:05.042
with a moldy leftover
ham and cheese sandwich.

10:05.709 --> 10:06.792
He's sorry.

10:06.876 --> 10:08.542
That's okay.

10:08.626 --> 10:09.751
Besides, I'm
too nervous to eat.

10:09.834 --> 10:11.584
Why are you nervous?
It's only an interview.

10:11.667 --> 10:12.792
It's not like
you don't have a job.

10:12.876 --> 10:14.709
Well, this is different.

10:14.792 --> 10:16.584
It's senior
creative director.

10:16.667 --> 10:18.250
It's the big time.

10:18.959 --> 10:20.292
It'll be all right, honey.

10:24.292 --> 10:25.709
Great city, isn't it?

10:25.792 --> 10:27.792
All I see is fog.

10:27.876 --> 10:29.626
PILOT: <i>Well, folks,</i>
<i>bad news this afternoon.</i>

10:29.709 --> 10:31.500
<i>New York is
completely fogged in.</i>

10:31.584 --> 10:34.292
<i>We've been diverted to
Logan Airport in Boston.</i>

10:34.375 --> 10:35.417
Boston?
Boston?

10:37.000 --> 10:38.125
We're here.
I'll see if
there's any flights

10:38.209 --> 10:39.292
going anywhere
near New York.

10:39.375 --> 10:40.792
All right,
and I'll get the bags.

10:40.876 --> 10:41.792
I'll meet you
at the carousel.

10:41.876 --> 10:43.083
Okay.

10:43.542 --> 10:44.584
Henry?

10:48.667 --> 10:50.334
Yes, I'm still
excited you came.

10:52.334 --> 10:53.375
Bags.

11:00.167 --> 11:01.209
Ooh!

11:02.167 --> 11:04.667
The buses are filled
until 3:00 in the morning.

11:04.751 --> 11:06.375
The next train to New York
from South Station

11:06.459 --> 11:07.876
is in 20 minutes.

11:17.667 --> 11:19.083
(WHISTLING)

11:22.000 --> 11:23.209
There's a train
in 20 minutes,

11:23.292 --> 11:24.792
gets us into New York...
Where are the bags?

11:24.876 --> 11:26.292
They didn't come out.

11:26.375 --> 11:28.000
What do you mean
they didn't come out?

11:28.083 --> 11:29.375
I can't say it any simpler
than that, Henry.

11:29.459 --> 11:31.000
They didn't come out.

11:31.083 --> 11:32.292
What do you mean
they didn't come out?

11:32.375 --> 11:34.042
Calm down, Henry.
How can I calm down?

11:34.125 --> 11:35.375
I've got to be in New York
tomorrow morning

11:35.459 --> 11:37.209
for the most important
interview of my...

11:37.292 --> 11:39.500
Just give me the claim...
The check... Give me...

11:39.584 --> 11:41.626
Henry!
Excuse me! Excuse me!

11:41.709 --> 11:43.083
Are there any more
bags up there?

11:43.167 --> 11:45.292
We were supposed to land...
Are you crazy?

11:45.375 --> 11:47.459
Listen, I'm Henry Clark
from Flight 42.

11:47.542 --> 11:48.876
It's 3-6-4...

11:48.959 --> 11:50.125
You're gonna
get hurt!

11:50.209 --> 11:52.334
...6-T-dash-7... Ohh!

11:56.042 --> 11:57.626
That's not our bag!

11:58.292 --> 12:00.500
Can you describe
the bags?

12:00.584 --> 12:03.042
Yes, I have
a brown suitcase,
a brown garment bag,

12:03.125 --> 12:05.042
and three blue sportsacs.

12:05.125 --> 12:07.000
Mr. Clark, many bags
look alike.

12:07.083 --> 12:09.209
It most cases,
specific descriptions

12:09.292 --> 12:12.250
lead to apprehending
the suspect.

12:12.334 --> 12:14.834
My bags didn't
murder anyone.
They just got lost.

12:14.918 --> 12:15.876
Henry,
look at this.

12:15.959 --> 12:17.667
All right, um,

12:17.751 --> 12:20.834
my suitcase looks
something like that.

12:20.918 --> 12:25.042
Would that be the 24-
or the 26-inch model?

12:25.125 --> 12:26.500
Gee, honey, in my rush
to leave the house,

12:26.584 --> 12:28.042
I forgot to
measure my bags.

12:28.125 --> 12:30.292
Oh, it looks
a little like this.

12:30.375 --> 12:32.584
It's kinda rough,
but it'll give you an idea.

12:32.667 --> 12:36.250
Wow! Are you an artist?

12:36.334 --> 12:38.584
Well, I used to be
in advertising
with my husband.

12:38.667 --> 12:40.918
This is
a fantastic drawing.

12:41.000 --> 12:42.375
Thank you.

12:42.459 --> 12:44.751
Unfortunately,
we don't have that bag.

12:45.709 --> 12:48.584
Where will you be staying
in the Boston area?

12:48.667 --> 12:51.959
In the Boston area,
we will be staying
in New York.

12:52.042 --> 12:54.459
Oh, Henry, calm down.
There's plenty of cabs.

12:54.542 --> 12:55.709
It's not worth getting
a heart attack over.

12:55.792 --> 12:57.209
I should have eaten.

12:57.292 --> 12:59.125
You know how dizzy I get
when I don't eat.
I'm reeling.

12:59.209 --> 13:00.876
I know.
Well, there's plenty
of food on the train.

13:00.959 --> 13:02.876
You just have to go
with the flow.

13:02.959 --> 13:04.292
All right, you're right,
you're right.

13:04.375 --> 13:05.751
I'm calming down.
I am going to calm down.

13:05.834 --> 13:07.083
Good.

13:07.167 --> 13:09.167
Thank you,
thank you.

13:10.375 --> 13:12.209
What's that taste?
What taste?

13:12.292 --> 13:13.459
Did you have
peanut butter?

13:13.542 --> 13:15.125
I don't know what
you're talking about.

13:15.209 --> 13:16.500
Where did you get
peanut butter?
I didn't.

13:16.584 --> 13:18.375
You usually don't taste
like peanut butter.

13:18.459 --> 13:19.876
That's it.
I'm throwing away
that lipstick.

13:19.959 --> 13:21.792
You had peanut butter.
I did not.

13:21.876 --> 13:24.042
Yes, you did.
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

13:24.125 --> 13:25.334
All right,
I confess, okay?

13:25.417 --> 13:26.959
I went to
the vending machine

13:27.042 --> 13:28.375
while I was waiting
for the bags.
Aha!

13:28.459 --> 13:30.125
I had 75 cents.

13:30.209 --> 13:31.876
I put it into
the vending machine,

13:31.959 --> 13:33.959
it didn't make change,
and so I ate them all!

13:34.042 --> 13:36.042
How many were there?
Two.

13:36.125 --> 13:37.626
Two? Well, I'm dizzy.

13:37.709 --> 13:39.209
Oh, Henry,
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

13:39.292 --> 13:40.709
It doesn't mean
I don't love you.

13:40.792 --> 13:43.083
I, uh, hate to interrupt,
but are we going anywhere?

13:43.167 --> 13:44.667
Oh, my God! I thought
we were already moving.

13:44.751 --> 13:46.417
South Station.
We have 10 minutes
to catch a train.

13:46.500 --> 13:48.250
Oh, my God!

13:52.500 --> 13:55.125
HENRY: Come on, come on,
we can make it!

13:58.417 --> 14:00.209
All right, all right.

14:01.417 --> 14:02.709
Aah!
Ohh!

14:04.626 --> 14:05.792
Did we miss it?

14:05.876 --> 14:08.876
Uh, the 3:38
to New York?

14:08.959 --> 14:10.667
Yeah.
We missed it.

14:10.751 --> 14:12.292
This can't be happening.

14:12.375 --> 14:14.292
Oh, Henry, if you're
a little late,

14:14.375 --> 14:15.834
they won't mind.
They'll understand.

14:15.918 --> 14:17.375
They do not
give a position
of responsibility

14:17.459 --> 14:19.584
to a man who cannot get
from Ohio to New York

14:19.667 --> 14:20.876
in 24 hours.

14:20.959 --> 14:22.459
But in the world
of advertising,

14:22.542 --> 14:24.292
I really don't think
that makes any difference.

14:24.375 --> 14:26.334
If you want to be
a messenger, maybe.

14:26.417 --> 14:27.918
Do I have time to
go to the bathroom?

14:28.000 --> 14:29.250
All the time
in the world.

14:29.334 --> 14:31.459
Okay. And don't worry, honey,

14:31.542 --> 14:33.125
