18:05.292 --> 18:06.417
♪<i> Love train</i> ♪

18:06.500 --> 18:08.959
♪<i> Mmm-mmm ♪</i>
<i>♪ Love</i> ♪

18:09.042 --> 18:10.167
♪<i> Oh, yeah</i> ♪

18:10.250 --> 18:13.083
<i>♪ Let it ride ♪</i>

18:13.876 --> 18:15.584
Boy, it's hot in here.

18:15.667 --> 18:18.375
Ohh! It tells you
everything about a heater

18:18.459 --> 18:20.459
except how to
shut it off.
Oh, perfect.

18:20.542 --> 18:22.250
Oh, Henry, what
are we gonna do?

18:22.334 --> 18:24.125
I'm melting
out of my dress.

18:24.209 --> 18:26.667
I don't understand.
It's got an engage switch
but no disengage.

18:26.751 --> 18:28.000
It's a thousand
degrees in here.

18:28.083 --> 18:30.083
It's like a setting
for a pot roast.

18:30.167 --> 18:31.876
Honey, it's freezing!
Put that up!

18:31.959 --> 18:33.626
It feels so good.

18:33.709 --> 18:35.042
Oh, jeez!

18:35.125 --> 18:37.792
(HEAVY METAL MUSIC PLAYS)

18:38.125 --> 18:39.334
(MUSIC CHANGES)

18:39.417 --> 18:40.542
<i>♪ Isn't it romantic? ♪</i>

18:40.626 --> 18:42.083
Ohh! Mmm!

18:47.751 --> 18:48.876
(SIGHS)

18:50.042 --> 18:52.042
Henry, are we in a rut?

18:52.125 --> 18:54.792
No way.
I might be in a rut,
but we're not in a rut.

18:54.876 --> 18:56.626
Why are you in a rut?

18:56.709 --> 18:58.584
Well, same thing
every day,

18:58.667 --> 19:00.042
knowing exactly
what to expect.

19:00.125 --> 19:01.667
That's a rut.

19:01.751 --> 19:04.167
Well, I'm in more
of a rut than you are,

19:04.250 --> 19:06.876
'cause every since
Alan's been gone,

19:06.959 --> 19:08.751
every morning I wake up

19:08.834 --> 19:11.209
and I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

19:11.292 --> 19:12.584
It's been one morning.

19:13.667 --> 19:15.792
Well, I didn't say
a long rut,

19:15.876 --> 19:17.542
but it's a start.

19:17.626 --> 19:19.250
So we're both in a rut.

19:19.334 --> 19:20.918
Separately.

19:21.000 --> 19:22.959
I might be in a rut
and you might be in a rut,

19:23.042 --> 19:24.709
but we are not in a rut,

19:24.792 --> 19:26.751
because if we were in
a rut, that would be...

19:26.834 --> 19:29.000
That would be
a real rut, Henry.

19:33.709 --> 19:36.042
<i>♪ Old black magic
has me in its spell ♪</i>

19:36.125 --> 19:37.500
HENRY: Okay, there's
a fork coming up.

19:37.584 --> 19:39.000
Which way do I go?

19:39.083 --> 19:40.667
Okay, um, do you see

19:40.751 --> 19:43.000
a sign that says,
"Cross Bronx Expressway"?

19:43.083 --> 19:44.000
Yes, ma'am, yes, ma'am.

19:44.083 --> 19:45.125
Good.

19:47.209 --> 19:49.876
Okay, go past that...
What do you mean
go past it?

19:49.959 --> 19:51.792
Then you'll hit
a sign that'll say
"Triborough Bridge."

19:51.876 --> 19:53.042
It'll take you
right into Manhattan.

19:53.125 --> 19:55.042
I already made the turn.

19:55.125 --> 19:57.125
What do you mean
you turned?
I made the turn.

19:57.209 --> 19:59.125
I didn't tell you to turn.
You implied it.

19:59.209 --> 20:00.751
I did not imply it.
You did, too.

20:00.834 --> 20:02.584
No, how can you
imply a turn?

20:02.667 --> 20:04.834
I wouldn't even know
how to imply a turn.

20:04.918 --> 20:06.751
Let me tell you,
you know how to
imply a turn.

20:06.834 --> 20:09.209
Is that a map
in front of you or what?

20:09.292 --> 20:11.459
Oh, well, gee,
I don't know, Henry.

20:11.542 --> 20:14.709
I'm not a cartographer,
but it looks like a map.

20:14.792 --> 20:16.375
It's got a lot of squiggly
little lines all over it.

20:16.459 --> 20:17.626
You want to see?

20:17.709 --> 20:19.876
Hey! That's not funny.

20:23.042 --> 20:25.959
<i>♪ Oh, you're the lover
I have waited for</i>

20:26.042 --> 20:30.000
<i>♪ You're the mate that
fate had me created for ♪</i>

20:30.083 --> 20:32.417
Okay, just stay
to the right,
right up here.

20:32.500 --> 20:35.751
Are you sure, Henry?
Why don't we use that
navigation system?

20:35.834 --> 20:37.834
Honey, I'm in charge
of the map now.

20:37.918 --> 20:40.334
You just go straight
across the Triborough Bridge,
onto the FDR,

20:40.417 --> 20:42.834
and we're right into
the heart of Manhattan.

20:42.918 --> 20:44.042
All right.

20:45.667 --> 20:47.209
Is that New York City
back there?

20:47.292 --> 20:49.417
What are you
talking about?

20:49.500 --> 20:51.918
Oh, no, this is the
George Washington Bridge.

20:52.042 --> 20:53.959
This map...
What do you mean,
the map?

20:54.042 --> 20:56.918
You think everything I do
is from reading the map?

21:01.167 --> 21:03.417
COMPUTER VOICE:
<i>Proceed down Grand Street.</i>

21:03.500 --> 21:05.083
"Proceed down
Grand Street."

21:05.167 --> 21:06.792
Oh, don't feel bad.

21:06.876 --> 21:09.417
He's obviously
been here before.
He knows the city.

21:09.500 --> 21:11.000
Well, I wouldn't have
been confused at all

21:11.083 --> 21:12.626
if we'd come into the city
the right way.

21:12.709 --> 21:14.626
Well, he is not confused.

21:15.959 --> 21:18.125
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

21:18.209 --> 21:20.375
Huh? It's French.
What's that?

21:20.459 --> 21:21.709
Here, just press
this over here.

21:21.792 --> 21:23.417
No, no, no, no,
don't press it.

21:23.500 --> 21:25.459
Why, Henry?
I don't know droit.

21:25.542 --> 21:26.834
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

21:28.000 --> 21:29.918
Oh, no!
What did he say?
What did he say?

21:30.000 --> 21:32.250
It's Chinese or something.
Find Spanish.
Just find Spanish.

21:32.334 --> 21:34.542
No, what's he saying?
Find Spanish.

21:34.626 --> 21:37.250
I can't find Spanish.
I don't know how
to work this thing.

21:37.334 --> 21:38.876
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

21:39.542 --> 21:41.125
I'll press...
I'll press that.

21:41.209 --> 21:42.584
Henry, do something!

21:42.667 --> 21:43.918
Nancy, Nancy!
Aah!

21:44.542 --> 21:46.167
Turn! Turn! Turn!

21:48.667 --> 21:50.083
Nancy, it's fish!

21:52.209 --> 21:53.959
Oh, my God! God!

21:54.042 --> 21:55.334
Aah!

21:55.417 --> 21:57.167
Put on the brake!
The brake!

21:57.250 --> 21:59.083
Aah!
Aah!

22:04.876 --> 22:07.042
(COMPUTER SPEAKING FRENCH)

22:09.375 --> 22:10.626
How's your nose, honey?

22:10.709 --> 22:12.876
It's tender to the touch,
just like me.

22:13.918 --> 22:18.292
What's the bill?
Oh, it's $2,200.

22:18.375 --> 22:19.500
I could have bought
a car for that.

22:19.584 --> 22:20.709
Oh, I know.

22:21.709 --> 22:24.250
Oh, look at New York.

22:24.334 --> 22:25.834
Where?

22:25.918 --> 22:27.626
Honey, I want
to get to the hotel.

22:27.709 --> 22:28.709
How do we get there?
That's very simple.

22:28.792 --> 22:30.375
The streets of New York

22:30.459 --> 22:31.792
are laid out
on a rigid grid.

22:31.876 --> 22:33.667
Yeah, like somebody
else I know.

22:33.751 --> 22:35.000
You want to get
there or not?

22:35.083 --> 22:38.626
Yes, I do. All right,
so we follow the rigid grid

22:38.709 --> 22:40.876
to Park Avenue
and 64th Street.

22:40.959 --> 22:42.834
But now, all right,
now wait, right now
we're at...

22:42.918 --> 22:44.626
No, don't look
around at the signs.

22:44.709 --> 22:45.959
That's how people know
you're from out of town.

22:46.042 --> 22:47.667
You don't want that.

22:47.751 --> 22:49.209
By the way, there's
a walk New Yorkers have.

22:49.292 --> 22:50.709
They never stroll.

22:50.792 --> 22:52.375
They always look like
they have someplace,

22:52.459 --> 22:53.709
you know, really
important to go to.

22:53.792 --> 22:55.292
Okay.
It's gotta be like, uh...

22:55.375 --> 22:56.751
It's, uh...

22:59.292 --> 23:01.709
(LAUGHING) Henry.

23:01.792 --> 23:03.542
You know, go ahead
and make fun, you know,

23:03.626 --> 23:06.125
but you walk like a tourist,
and that's how you get
in trouble.

23:11.792 --> 23:13.918
Excuse me. I'm terribly
sorry to disturb you.

23:14.000 --> 23:16.167
I can't tell you how
embarrassing this is.

23:16.250 --> 23:19.209
I just left all my money
and credit cards in a cab.

23:19.292 --> 23:21.709
I'm late to a rehearsal.
I've got a play on Broadway
at the moment.

23:21.792 --> 23:23.417
If I could borrow
$5.00 for a taxi,

23:23.500 --> 23:24.918
you can come with me
to the theater.

23:25.000 --> 23:26.083
I will pay you back there.
You expect us
to believe this?

23:29.083 --> 23:31.709
No. No, I suppose not.
I'm sorry to have
bothered you.

23:31.792 --> 23:33.834
What play?
Nancy, there's no play.

23:33.918 --> 23:35.083
Actually, it's a revival

23:35.167 --> 23:37.834
of <i>Jesus Christ Superstar</i>
at the Broadhurst Theater.

23:37.918 --> 23:39.250
Do come if you
get the chance.

23:39.334 --> 23:41.459
Wait a minute.
<i>Jesus Christ Superstar?</i>

23:41.542 --> 23:43.125
Oh, my God. Are you
Andrew Lloyd Webber?

23:44.209 --> 23:45.709
Yes... Thank you. I...

23:45.792 --> 23:47.709
Oh, honey, it's
Andrew Lloyd Webber!

23:47.792 --> 23:49.792
We go into previews
next week, and as I said...

23:49.876 --> 23:51.584
We love
<i>Jesus Christ Superstar.</i>

23:51.667 --> 23:53.876
We saw
<i>Phantom of the Opera.</i>
And <i>Evita.</i>

23:53.959 --> 23:56.167
And <i>Evita.</i>
That was so great.

23:56.250 --> 23:58.250
And <i>Cats...</i>
Ohhh...

23:58.334 --> 24:00.500
Oh, honey, that was just...

24:00.584 --> 24:02.500
It hit so home for us.

24:02.584 --> 24:04.334
We lost a cat that year.

24:04.417 --> 24:06.209
It didn't sing
like your cats.

24:06.292 --> 24:07.876
I'm Henry Clark, and
this is my wife Nancy.

24:07.959 --> 24:09.542
A pleasure
to meet you both.

24:09.626 --> 24:12.000
We'd be honored
to lend you anything.

24:12.083 --> 24:14.250
No. Please. You mustn't
take out an open wallet
in the city,

24:14.334 --> 24:16.125
no matter how much
the crime rate's dropped.

24:16.209 --> 24:18.417
Yeah, well, I...
I entered Yokelville.

24:18.500 --> 24:19.876
Come on... Come over here.
Come on.

24:20.000 --> 24:22.042
I am so embarrassed
about this.

24:22.125 --> 24:23.959
No, don't be embarrassed.
When we tell the people
in Ohio

24:24.042 --> 24:25.459
that we lent
Andrew Lloyd Webber five...

24:25.542 --> 24:26.792
Sir Andrew Lloyd Webber...

24:26.876 --> 24:28.500
Sir. Sir...
No, it's Lord.

24:28.584 --> 24:30.292
I think he's a Lord.
Sir Lord.

24:30.375 --> 24:31.709
Sir Lord. You know
Paul McCartney?

24:31.792 --> 24:33.000
All right, shut up.

24:33.083 --> 24:34.417
What's he like?
Is he, like, fun...

24:34.500 --> 24:36.792
Shut up. Shut up!
What? Jesus!

24:36.876 --> 24:39.083
Give me...
Give it to me!

24:39.167 --> 24:40.417
Give me the bag.

24:40.500 --> 24:41.751
Give me the bag.
Give me...

24:41.834 --> 24:44.792
Give him the bag!
Hey... Oh, my God!

24:44.876 --> 24:47.626
Ohh! Why are you
doing this?

24:47.709 --> 24:49.709
Every show you do
is a hit!

24:50.292 --> 24:51.876
HENRY: Hey!
Henry!

24:51.959 --> 24:54.292
Henry, Andrew Lloyd Webber
just stole my pocketbook!

24:54.375 --> 24:56.876
He's not Andrew Lloyd Webber.
He's just a common criminal.

24:56.959 --> 24:58.751
Oh, Henry. I have
jelly legs, honey!

24:58.834 --> 25:00.042
Come on. Let's
get outta here.

25:00.125 --> 25:01.751
What are we
gonna do, Henry?

25:01.834 --> 25:04.083
Here. Here.
Okay. Okay, watch.

25:04.876 --> 25:06.000
What are you
doing, Henry?

25:06.083 --> 25:07.417
Credit card.
I put it in my sock

25:07.500 --> 25:08.667
when we were
on the plane.

25:08.751 --> 25:10.167
Oh! You're a genius!

25:10.250 --> 25:12.375
Thank you, thank you.
My God! You're a genius!

25:12.459 --> 25:14.834
Put it away! We might run
into Stephen Sondheim.

25:23.417 --> 25:24.626
Hello.
Hello.

25:28.000 --> 25:29.167
Ohhh...

25:34.292 --> 25:36.792
Oh, thank God. Look!

25:36.876 --> 25:38.209
Look at this place.

25:38.292 --> 25:40.500
Oh, it's beautiful.

25:40.584 --> 25:42.751
Oh, it's good
to be inside.

25:42.834 --> 25:44.500
Michelle, is that
a new haircut?

25:44.584 --> 25:46.042
Yes, it is.

25:46.125 --> 25:47.584
I think you'd better
stay in the back
for a while.

25:47.667 --> 25:49.209
(DING)

25:49.292 --> 25:51.709
Good evening. Welcome
to the Grand Mark Hotel.

25:51.792 --> 25:53.000
How may I be
of service to you?

25:53.083 --> 25:54.500
We have a reservation.
Clark.

25:56.125 --> 25:57.834
My name is Mersault,
the manager of the hotel.

25:57.918 --> 25:59.584
Yes, here we are.
Mr. and Mrs. Clark.

25:59.667 --> 26:01.209
If there's anything
at all I can do

26:01.292 --> 26:02.918
to make your stay
more pleasant,

26:03.000 --> 26:04.334
please don't hesitate
to let me know.

26:04.417 --> 26:05.876
That would be
room service.

26:05.959 --> 26:07.209
We haven't eaten
since this morning.

